hello I'm Shree a cloud Support Engineer
here at the AWS headquarters in Seattle
sometimes customers ask me why they
can't delete a hosted zone created by
ECS service from the route 53 console I
tell them whenever a route 53 hosted
zone is created by easy a service
discovery that zone can be managed only
by service discovery this means that
there are only two possible ways to
manage the hosted zone using service
discovery API calls or using the cloud
map service console today I'll show you
how to delete such a hosted zone created
by service discovery why are a w s cloud
map service console let's get started
after signing in to the AWS management
console navigate to the AWS cloud map
console in the navigation pane choose
namespaces choose the option for the
namespace that you want to delete choose
delete confirm that you want to delete
the service if you happen to stumble
upon this error while deleting the
namespace choose the namespace and make
sure that you delete the service under
this namespace you may want to
deregister
any instance if they are registered
within the service the namespace may
take a moment to get deleted on the AWS
cloud map service console now that your
namespace is deleted you may navigate to
route 53 console to see the hosted zone
as being deleted as well note that the
hosted zone for the given namespace
doesn't exist in Amazon route 53 console
anymore thanks for watching and happy
cloud computing from all of us here at
aw
